Credit Line: The Jefferson R. Burdick Collection, Gift of Jefferson R. Burdick
Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History: The United States and Canada, 1800–1900 A.D.
Description: Trade cards from the "Yacht Colors of the World" series (N91), issued in a set of 50 cards in 1889 to promote Duke's Cigarettes. Each card depicts a famous actress or beauty dressed in the colors of a specific yacht club.
